<font color="#FF0000">THE AIR IS CLEANER!</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan 11 21:50:23 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
On two different occassions I was written up for the CMH..both times is was denied..not reduced to a lower decoration..just denied.  The reports were simply destroyed..because &quot;we&quot; were not in Cambodia!<br><br>
I will never forget going after the Seventh Special Forces sniper that I rescued or the POWs.  More importantly they will never forget me.  The sniper, &quot;Spooky&quot; was/is one of the toughest men on Earth... he still remembers my name and call sign.  He broke down and cried when he introduced me to his wife and children.  No decoration could ever convey so much.<br><br>
Because of vets like O.D., SW, Cookie, Tom, Chet, Art, Doc Del,Paul, John, Class Lass, Toon Sarge, Dan and too many others to list here... I am honored every day.  When I walk in the presence of fine warriors I am humbled.  When I see strong men bend to help the weak I remember Glory.  When I see the rolls of the dead, I am grateful to have been lifted above the crimson tide.  When I see the wounded and scared looking for ways to ensure future peace I am proud.. and hopeful!<br><br>
There is no nice, clean, civil, philosophical, justifiable, merciful, holy way to kill people who violently disagree in idealogies...but perhaps there is a way to learn to disagree without violence.  The true tragedy, I fear, is that we will never learn how to do it!<br><br>
Jed you are not excluded from that list of men that I cited above...it is just that you and I, today, face different enemy targets.. ignorance, greed, immorality, and mistruths.<br><br>
The site is progressing in a favorable direction because of the strengths of good men and women.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
